# Theming

The entire visual identity of Cascade Goods is driven by CSS custom properties inside the `@theme { ... }` block in [src/index.css](mdc:src/index.css). Every component reads colors, radii, and fonts through these tokens, so re-theming should touch one file.

## When asked to re-theme (e.g. "re-theme this site in Salesforce blue")

1. Edit only the values inside `@theme { ... }` in [src/index.css](mdc:src/index.css). Do not modify component files.
2. Update the brand, accent, and supporting surface/border tokens together so the palette stays coordinated.
3. Verify contrast: each `*-foreground` token must remain readable against its paired background token.
4. If you find yourself wanting to change a component file to apply the new theme, the token system is missing a token — add the token in `index.css` and reference it from the component instead.

## Using tokens in components

Reference tokens via Tailwind's arbitrary value syntax:

```tsx
<button className="bg-[var(--color-brand)] text-[var(--color-brand-foreground)] rounded-[var(--radius-md)]">
  Add to cart
</button>
```

Never introduce hardcoded colors (`bg-blue-500`, `text-[#1f2937]`, etc.) in components. If a needed color isn't covered by an existing token in [src/index.css](mdc:src/index.css), add a new token there first, then reference it.
